                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12548731" author="jimk" created="Wed, 5 Dec 2007 17:10:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, since there is one memcache per column, this could be set on a per column basis&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12565243" author="bryanduxbury" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2008 01:40:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After all the work we&apos;ve been doing with trying to optimize flush/compact/split sizes, this issue seems risky. Exposing this tuning parameter could really allow someone to damage their HBase instance. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12581326" author="bryanduxbury" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2008 03:24:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What kind of use case would benefit from changing the memcache size? Also, this issue might significantly interfere with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-512&quot; title=&quot;Add configuration for global aggregate memcache size&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-512&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-512&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614256" author="stack" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2008 07:11:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolved by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-62&quot; title=&quot;[hbase] Allow user add arbitrary key/value pairs to table and column descriptors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-62&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-62&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; commit.  Thanks for the patch Andrew.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
